# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#ActiveDevice
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ActiveDevice> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ActiveDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Device> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ActiveDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A medical device whose operation depends on a source of energy other than that generated by the human body or gravity."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ActiveDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Active Device"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#ActiveImplantDevice
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ActiveImplantDevice> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ActiveImplantDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#ActiveDevice> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ActiveImplantDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#ImplantableDevice> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ActiveImplantDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> _:genid1 .
_:genid1 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#hasValue> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
_:genid1 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty> <http://www.example.org/emdco#isActive> .
_:genid1 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ActiveImplantDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> _:genid2 .
_:genid2 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#hasValue> "true"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
_:genid2 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty> <http://www.example.org/emdco#isImplantable> .
_:genid2 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ActiveImplantDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A device that is both active and implantable, such as pacemakers or ventricular assist devices."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ActiveImplantDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Active Implant Device"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#ContaminationRisk
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ContaminationRisk> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ContaminationRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ContaminationRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk from reagent or product contamination leading to systematic errors."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ContaminationRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Contamination Risk"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#CybersecurityRisk
<http://www.example.org/emdco#CybersecurityRisk> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#CybersecurityRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#CybersecurityRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk from exploitable software vulnerabilities enabling unauthorised device access."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#CybersecurityRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Cybersecurity Risk"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#Device
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Device> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Device> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#MedicalEntity> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Device> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> _:genid3 .
_:genid3 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#minCardinality> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger> .
_:genid3 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty> <http://www.example.org/emdco#hasManufacturer> .
_:genid3 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Device> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A medical device as defined by MDR (EU 2017/745) or IVDR (EU 2017/746)."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Device> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Device"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#DiagnosticRisk
<http://www.example.org/emdco#DiagnosticRisk> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#DiagnosticRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#DiagnosticRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk of diagnostic error including false positive or false negative results from IVD devices."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#DiagnosticRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Diagnostic Risk"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#FieldSafetyCorrectiveAction
<http://www.example.org/emdco#FieldSafetyCorrectiveAction> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#FieldSafetyCorrectiveAction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#MedicalEntity> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#FieldSafetyCorrectiveAction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An action taken by a manufacturer to reduce a risk of death or serious deterioration associated with the use of a device already placed on the market (FSCA)."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#FieldSafetyCorrectiveAction> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Field Safety Corrective Action"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#IVDRRiskClass
<http://www.example.org/emdco#IVDRRiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#IVDRRiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#RiskClass> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#IVDRRiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk classification under Regulation EU 2017/746 (IVDR): Class A, B, C, D."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#IVDRRiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "IVDR Risk Class"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#ImplantableDevice
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ImplantableDevice> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ImplantableDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Device> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ImplantableDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A device intended to be totally or partially introduced into the human body and intended to remain there after the procedure."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#ImplantableDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Implantable Device"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#InSituCorrection
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InSituCorrection> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InSituCorrection> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#FieldSafetyCorrectiveAction> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InSituCorrection> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A corrective action performed on a device while it remains in use, such as software updates or protocol changes."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InSituCorrection> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "In Situ Correction"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#InVitroDiagnosticDevice
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InVitroDiagnosticDevice> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InVitroDiagnosticDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Device> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InVitroDiagnosticDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A device intended for examination of specimens derived from the human body, regulated under IVDR (EU 2017/746)."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InVitroDiagnosticDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "In Vitro Diagnostic Device"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#Incident
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Incident> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Incident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#MedicalEntity> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Incident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> _:genid4 .
_:genid4 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#someValuesFrom> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Device> .
_:genid4 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty> <http://www.example.org/emdco#involvedDevice> .
_:genid4 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Incident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A malfunction or deterioration in the characteristics of a device which has led or could lead to the death or serious injury of a patient."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Incident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Incident"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#InfectionRisk
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InfectionRisk> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InfectionRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InfectionRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk of device-related infection including site infection, sepsis or biofilm formation."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InfectionRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Infection Risk"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#InjuryRisk
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InjuryRisk> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InjuryRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InjuryRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk of direct physical harm or injury to the patient caused by the device."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InjuryRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Injury Risk"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#InterferenceRisk
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InterferenceRisk> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InterferenceRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InterferenceRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk from electromagnetic interference or MRI-related artefacts affecting device performance."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#InterferenceRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Interference Risk"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#MDRRiskClass
<http://www.example.org/emdco#MDRRiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#MDRRiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#RiskClass> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#MDRRiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk classification under Regulation EU 2017/745 (MDR): Class I, IIa, IIb, III."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#MDRRiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "MDR Risk Class"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#MalfunctionRisk
<http://www.example.org/emdco#MalfunctionRisk> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#MalfunctionRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#MalfunctionRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk arising from device malfunction or failure to perform as intended."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#MalfunctionRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Malfunction Risk"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#Manufacturer
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Manufacturer> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Manufacturer> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#MedicalEntity> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Manufacturer> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A natural or legal person who manufactures or fully refurbishes a device or has a device designed, manufactured or fully refurbished."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Manufacturer> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Manufacturer"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#MaterialRisk
<http://www.example.org/emdco#MaterialRisk> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#MaterialRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#MaterialRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk from wear debris, corrosion or adverse tissue reaction to implant materials."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#MaterialRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Material Risk"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#MedicalEntity
<http://www.example.org/emdco#MedicalEntity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#MedicalEntity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Top-level class for all entities in the medical device domain."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#MedicalEntity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Medical Entity"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#NearMissIncident
<http://www.example.org/emdco#NearMissIncident> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#NearMissIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Incident> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#NearMissIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An incident where a potential harm did not reach the patient due to fortunate circumstances or corrective action."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#NearMissIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Near Miss Incident"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#RadiationRisk
<http://www.example.org/emdco#RadiationRisk> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#RadiationRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#RadiationRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk of unintended ionising or non-ionising radiation exposure."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#RadiationRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Radiation Risk"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#Recall
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Recall> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Recall> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#FieldSafetyCorrectiveAction> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Recall> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A corrective action to return or replace devices already distributed due to a safety issue."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Recall> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Recall"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#MedicalEntity> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An identified risk associated with a medical device, classified according to IMDRF nomenclature."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Risk"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#RiskClass
<http://www.example.org/emdco#RiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#RiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Classification of medical device risk level as defined by MDR or IVDR."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#RiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Risk Class"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#SafetyAlert
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SafetyAlert> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SafetyAlert> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#FieldSafetyCorrectiveAction> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SafetyAlert> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A communication issued to healthcare professionals or users regarding updated safety guidance for a device."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SafetyAlert> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Safety Alert"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#SelfTestDevice
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SelfTestDevice> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SelfTestDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#InVitroDiagnosticDevice> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SelfTestDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An IVD device intended for use by lay persons in a home environment."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SelfTestDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Self-Test Device"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#SeriousIncident
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SeriousIncident> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SeriousIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Incident> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SeriousIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An incident that directly or indirectly led to the death, serious injury, or serious deterioration in the health of a patient."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SeriousIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Serious Incident"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#SingleUseDevice
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SingleUseDevice> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SingleUseDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Device> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SingleUseDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A device intended to be used on one individual during a single procedure."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SingleUseDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Single Use Device"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#SoftwareRisk
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SoftwareRisk> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SoftwareRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SoftwareRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk arising from software malfunction including incorrect dosing or alarming."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SoftwareRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Software Risk"@en .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#UserNotice
<http://www.example.org/emdco#UserNotice> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#UserNotice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#FieldSafetyCorrectiveAction> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#UserNotice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A field safety notice issued to device users or operators providing updated usage instructions."@en .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#UserNotice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "User Notice"@en .
